cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text classification. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approach to learning and generalizing to unseen classes. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing models capable of predicting unseen classes. It could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with categorizing text and retrieving relevant information. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed approach involves embedding sentences and tags into a shared space, which is a common technique used in computer vision tasks.
